com.vernalis.pdbconnector.config

Class QueryOption

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vernalis.pdbconnector.config.QueryOption
  • Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public class QueryOption
extends java.lang.Object
    QueryOption class. QueryOption represents a single query option in the dialog. Each query option is displayed in a separate, bordered, subpanel of the parent query category tab. Example query options include:
    • Text search
    • SMILES/SMARTS search
    • Molecular weight search
    A QueryOption contains the list of (user input) query parameters that are required to define the query, as well as the XML query string that should be passed to the PDB web service. The XML query string is stored with placeholders for each query parameter argument. The placeholders are substituted with the actual argument values at runtime.
    See Also:
    QueryCategory, QueryParam
